pgrep -a syslog

will give you all the dtailsof the process

NiceNess:

Niceness value can be between -20 to +19

Higher nice value = lower proririty

ex nice -n 11 bash, whwere nice is the cmd and 11 is the nice value for bash process.
ps l >>>shows nice values
ps aux shows all values
ps -U aaron >>shows user specific

ps lax >>all with nice values

To see forest like processes that will show all parent processes and the child process please use the f option.
Ex:
ps fax
renice to add the nice value to an existing process.

Ex:
renice 7 8789

where 8789 is the PID

Only a root user can change nice values which are very low so that their priority is high.The regular user can change the pririty or renice only once.

